WEBVTT

00:01.652 --> 00:03.652
             [♪♪♪]

00:05.388 --> 00:06.855
            [WHISTLES]

00:07.424 --> 00:09.158
                  Whoa. Wha--?

00:09.160 --> 00:11.026
      Would you like
some hot chocolate, master?

00:11.028 --> 00:13.428
      Well, thank you, Jeannie.
    You shouldn't have bothered.

00:13.430 --> 00:15.463
  Oh, it was no bother.

00:15.465 --> 00:17.132
         Is there anything else
            you would like?

00:17.134 --> 00:18.901
Uh, no, no. You've--
You've done enough.

00:18.903 --> 00:21.170
 Oh, I wanna thank you for
that wonderful dinner I had.

00:21.172 --> 00:22.304
       Oh, it was my pleasure.

00:22.306 --> 00:23.471
       Mm-hm.

00:23.473 --> 00:24.706
 Hey, that's good.

00:24.708 --> 00:27.042
        And, uh,
for pressing my clothes.

00:27.044 --> 00:28.510
  Oh, well I enjoyed it.

00:28.512 --> 00:31.180
      And for cleaning the house
         and washing the car.

00:31.182 --> 00:32.714
           You really didn't--

00:32.716 --> 00:34.016
   You didn't have
   to go that far.

00:34.018 --> 00:36.084
 Oh, that is what I am here for.
          To please you.

00:36.086 --> 00:37.786
  Oh, you please me,
      very much.

00:37.788 --> 00:39.888
              Oh, I am glad.

00:39.890 --> 00:42.257
         On Haji's birthday,
    you wished to get rid of me.

00:42.259 --> 00:43.792
       I, uh--
  Well, I know that.

00:43.794 --> 00:44.793
I'm sorry, but, well,

00:44.795 --> 00:46.628
    when you cause
one of your disasters,

00:46.630 --> 00:48.763
it makes me a little nervous,
         that's all.

00:48.765 --> 00:50.465
I really couldn't get along
       without you.

00:50.467 --> 00:52.835
     Oh, you will never have
to get along without me, master.

00:52.837 --> 00:55.137
Good, good. I-- I like things
 just the way they are now.

00:55.139 --> 00:56.604
  Quiet and peaceful,
       you know.

00:56.606 --> 00:57.605
                 Do you, master?

00:57.607 --> 00:59.208
     'Course I do.
       Don't you?

00:59.210 --> 01:01.109
                  Oh, yes, yes.
                   If you do.

01:01.111 --> 01:02.244
  Where'd I get this?

01:02.246 --> 01:03.511
         Yeah.

01:03.513 --> 01:05.680
     Well, if you do not need me
         any longer, master,

01:05.682 --> 01:06.681
               I will go to bed.

01:06.683 --> 01:08.083
                    [YAWNING]
                       Oh.

01:08.085 --> 01:09.184
                    Good night,
                      master.

01:09.186 --> 01:11.002
      Good night.

01:11.004 --> 01:12.503
     Before you-

01:16.009 --> 01:19.010
<i> The Care and Feeding</i>
     <i> of Genies.</i>

01:19.012 --> 01:22.047
 Oh, this must be the book
Roger sent me for Christmas.

01:23.550 --> 01:26.084
    Let's see, "Blessed is he
         who has a genie

01:26.086 --> 01:27.853
     "to do his bidding,
        but woe to him

01:27.855 --> 01:29.621
      who lets his genie
   get the better of him."

01:29.623 --> 01:31.056
            [LAUGHS]

01:31.058 --> 01:33.291
         That was written
          by an expert.

01:33.293 --> 01:35.727
        "And it is written
   that only the spell of Haji

01:35.729 --> 01:37.595
     "can take away the power
           of a genie.

01:37.597 --> 01:39.297
           "If, however,
     a genie marries a mortal,

01:39.299 --> 01:40.832
   its power vanishes forever."

01:40.834 --> 01:42.400
 Yeah, I remember old Haji.

01:42.402 --> 01:43.769
             Um...

01:43.771 --> 01:46.404
       "A genie is full
     of tricks and wiles.

01:46.406 --> 01:48.640
       "If its master...

01:48.642 --> 01:50.642
             [♪♪♪]

01:57.484 --> 01:59.584
      "It is written that only
         the spell of Haji

01:59.586 --> 02:01.253
          "can take away
      the power of a genie.

02:01.255 --> 02:03.288
           "If, however,
     a genie marries a mortal,

02:03.290 --> 02:05.356
    its power vanishes forever."

02:08.044 --> 02:10.178
 Jeannie? Jeannie.

02:10.180 --> 02:11.847
         Oh.

02:11.849 --> 02:13.649
Jeannie, I gotta talk to you.
                 [YAWNS]

02:13.651 --> 02:15.918
  I gotta talk to you--
      Is anything wrong, master?

02:15.920 --> 02:17.920
Yeah, did you know that
if you married a mortal,

02:17.922 --> 02:19.354
you wouldn't be
a genie anymore?

02:19.356 --> 02:21.790
                  Oh, yes,
           any genie knows that.

02:21.792 --> 02:23.358
   But is it true,
    really true?

02:23.360 --> 02:24.860
           Well, of course. Why?

02:24.862 --> 02:26.628
   Well, don't make
any plans for tomorrow.

02:26.630 --> 02:28.030
You and I are getting married.

02:28.032 --> 02:29.031
       Married!

02:29.033 --> 02:30.298
       [LAUGHS]

02:34.921 --> 02:36.921
             [♪♪♪]

03:23.153 --> 03:25.153
             [♪♪♪]

03:29.209 --> 03:31.209
             [♪♪♪]

03:32.379 --> 03:34.712
         Tomorrow night?
      No, no, no, I'm busy.

03:34.714 --> 03:35.847
                    Roge.

03:35.849 --> 03:37.949
      Busy, yes.

03:37.951 --> 03:39.951
Uh, how 'bout next week, okay?

03:42.356 --> 03:43.454
  [SIGHS]

03:43.456 --> 03:46.358
Yes, you know I love you.

03:46.360 --> 03:48.726
Goodbye, mother.

03:48.728 --> 03:50.061
 Well, what's up?

03:50.063 --> 03:52.063
       How would you like to fly
          to Maryland with me?

03:52.065 --> 03:53.598
    To Maryland?
Do we have a mission?

03:53.600 --> 03:54.766
                    I do,
            I'm getting married.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.368
You're kidding.
                   [CHUCKLING]
                      Yeah.

03:56.370 --> 03:57.402
           I'm marrying Jeannie.

03:57.404 --> 03:58.870
     Jeannie?
                      Yeah.

03:58.872 --> 04:00.138
     Our Jeannie?

04:00.140 --> 04:02.240
             Yeah, that's right.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.541
 Now, listen to me.

04:03.543 --> 04:05.610
  Now, listen to me
    very closely.

04:05.612 --> 04:07.712
Jeannie's done something
to you to make you think

04:07.714 --> 04:09.347
you're going to marry her.

04:09.349 --> 04:12.083
       But you're not,
because I'm going to save you.

04:12.085 --> 04:14.252
                Yeah, Roger,
            I want to marry her.

04:15.989 --> 04:17.389
Come on, you gotta snap out
          of it!

04:17.391 --> 04:18.990
  You're under a spell,
    can you hear me?

04:18.992 --> 04:20.058
                 Roger, Roger!

04:20.060 --> 04:21.858
                I can hear you,
               there's no spell.

04:21.861 --> 04:23.328
    The whole thing was my idea.

04:23.330 --> 04:24.796
           Your idea?
        Are you kidding?

04:24.798 --> 04:26.864
       You know you can't
 marry Jeannie. She's a genie.

04:26.866 --> 04:28.733
        Well, she's not gonna be
            a genie anymore.

04:28.735 --> 04:29.867
               I just found out.

04:29.869 --> 04:31.937
        If she marries a mortal,
        she stops being a genie.

04:31.939 --> 04:33.071
  Yeah, who told you that?

04:33.073 --> 04:34.239
            I read it in a book.

04:34.241 --> 04:36.942
  Yeah, well, I bet she--
    She wrote the book.

04:36.944 --> 04:38.243
                 Oh, brother.

04:38.245 --> 04:39.610
       Oh, wait a minute.

04:39.612 --> 04:41.947
        Oh, well, let's not rush
           into these things.

04:41.949 --> 04:44.049
    Why don't you think about it
       for a couple of years,

04:44.051 --> 04:46.418
        then you can marry her--
Roger, I'm marrying Jeannie.

04:46.420 --> 04:48.370
 Now, are you gonna be
  my best man or not?

04:48.372 --> 04:51.740
   Well, if I can't stop you,
   I might as well join you.

04:51.742 --> 04:53.158
         Thanks, Roge.

04:53.160 --> 04:55.460
     Got yourself a best man.

04:55.462 --> 04:56.495
         Well, thanks.

04:56.497 --> 04:57.662
         I'll, uh, also

04:57.664 --> 04:59.748
     keep myself available
    for your court-martial.

04:59.750 --> 05:01.315
      Oh, there's nothing
        to worry about.

05:01.317 --> 05:02.617
Once Jeannie and I are married,

05:02.619 --> 05:04.503
      she'll be an average,
       everyday housewife.

05:04.505 --> 05:06.872
   Uh, what time are we leaving?
 Look at this. Huh?

05:06.874 --> 05:07.939
       What time are we leaving?

05:07.941 --> 05:09.007
 Four o'clock plane.

05:09.009 --> 05:10.509
    Ah, that gives me six hours.

05:10.511 --> 05:11.710
Yeah, to do what?

05:11.712 --> 05:13.645
         Uh, well, I've got
        a few calls to make.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.614
            [CHUCKLES]
          See you later.

05:15.616 --> 05:17.916
     [CHUCKLING]
    Look at this.

05:17.918 --> 05:19.751
                 [CHUCKLES]
               It's my office.

05:21.555 --> 05:22.787
         [CHUCKLING]
           See ya.

05:23.690 --> 05:25.690
             [♪♪♪]

05:32.699 --> 05:34.583
           Jeannie,
    I've gotta talk to ya.

05:34.585 --> 05:37.986
  Did Major Nelson tell you that
 we are getting married tonight?

05:37.988 --> 05:39.821
   He did mention it.

05:39.823 --> 05:41.990
        Oh, isn't that exciting?

05:41.992 --> 05:43.758
      [SCREAMS]
    You don't know how exciting.

05:43.760 --> 05:45.711
      A former astronaut married
              to a genie.

05:45.713 --> 05:48.379
 Yes, is it not wonderful?

05:48.381 --> 05:50.315
        A form--

05:50.317 --> 05:52.134
   A former astronaut?

05:52.136 --> 05:53.701
            They won't keep him
              in the program

05:53.703 --> 05:54.970
            when they find out
                about you.

05:54.972 --> 05:56.637
      But why not?

05:56.639 --> 05:58.357
   I will no longer be
        a genie.

05:58.359 --> 06:00.659
                  Oh, great.
              That's just great.

06:00.661 --> 06:04.262
       Oh, great, a former genie
        married to an astronaut.

06:04.264 --> 06:05.964
           I mean, how could you
              do this to him?

06:05.966 --> 06:07.315
  But I love him.

06:07.317 --> 06:10.285
         And he loves me.
    He asked me to marry him.

06:10.287 --> 06:12.220
     Jeannie, the only reason
        he's marrying you

06:12.222 --> 06:14.455
   is because he has some crazy
    idea that when you marry,

06:14.457 --> 06:15.874
   you won't be a genie anymore.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.292
       But it is true.

06:17.294 --> 06:18.493
           How do you know?

06:18.495 --> 06:19.661
    It is in our legend.

06:19.663 --> 06:21.363
            Do you mean,

06:21.365 --> 06:23.365
     you're gonna jeopardize
       Tony's whole career

06:23.367 --> 06:24.883
           on a legend
     you're not even sure of?

06:24.885 --> 06:27.552
 I know how I can find out.

06:27.554 --> 06:29.504
           Haji.
            Who's Haji?

06:29.506 --> 06:31.006
 He is the master
of all the genies.

06:31.008 --> 06:32.374
He is most powerful.

06:32.376 --> 06:34.575
      Yeah, well, why don't you
    talk to him, and I can leave

06:34.577 --> 06:36.144
                and then maybe
               I comfort you--

06:38.098 --> 06:40.598
Oh, thank you, Haji,
  for coming here.

06:40.600 --> 06:42.000
I hope it's something important.

06:42.002 --> 06:43.701
      This is my busy time
         of the month.

06:43.703 --> 06:44.853
          Who's this?

06:44.855 --> 06:46.654
           Oh, I'm, uh,
     Major Roger Healey, sir.

06:46.656 --> 06:48.607
   I'm on detached duty to NASA.

06:48.609 --> 06:49.741
               Yes.

06:50.527 --> 06:52.194
     Why did you call me?

06:52.196 --> 06:53.495
        I need your help.

06:53.497 --> 06:55.280
         I am thinking
     about getting married.

06:55.282 --> 06:57.365
         Ah, excellent.

06:57.367 --> 06:58.917
         Ha-ha, it's about time.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.969
   I knew you would soon tire
    of your dog of a master.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.674
   You are going to marry Ali,
         the tent-maker?

07:05.676 --> 07:07.008
            Uh, no.

07:07.010 --> 07:09.544
    Omar, the oasis keeper?

07:09.546 --> 07:10.595
              No.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.848
    Sharif, the camel king?

07:12.850 --> 07:15.100
             Mm, no.

07:15.102 --> 07:16.468
         No? Then who?

07:16.470 --> 07:18.035
    Tony, the dog of a master.

07:18.888 --> 07:20.439
                  What?

07:20.441 --> 07:23.225
     You are going to marry
          your master?

07:23.227 --> 07:25.310
            Oh, yes.
         [HAJI GROANS]

07:25.312 --> 07:27.378
         Is it not true
   that if I marry my master,

07:27.380 --> 07:29.364
   I will lose all my powers
          as a genie?

07:29.366 --> 07:31.032
     Yes, it is so written.

07:31.034 --> 07:32.367
         Ha. You see?

07:32.369 --> 07:34.202
         Well, I don't care
      if it's written or not.

07:34.204 --> 07:36.288
        I think the marriage
      is gonna be a disaster.

07:36.290 --> 07:37.622
              [CHUCKLES]

07:37.624 --> 07:40.792
    And I say, I would make
    Major Nelson very happy.

07:40.794 --> 07:42.794
           Well, it's my opinion
           against your opinion.

07:42.796 --> 07:45.046
 And that's a draw. Let's forget
      about the whole thing.

07:45.048 --> 07:47.549
                 Yes.
      Uh, one moment.

07:47.551 --> 07:50.335
 Is it possible for you to show
   him what it would be like?

07:50.337 --> 07:51.336
              Ha.

07:51.338 --> 07:52.737
    Haji could do anything.

07:54.892 --> 07:56.324
             [♪♪♪]

07:56.326 --> 07:57.625
       Hey. Look at that, very--

07:57.627 --> 07:59.194
            Quiet!

07:59.196 --> 08:00.362
         Shh.

08:00.364 --> 08:01.662
          Watch.

08:03.000 --> 08:06.201
           [WAILS]

08:06.203 --> 08:08.036
          [MUTTERING]

08:10.573 --> 08:13.141
  Look into the crystal ball.

08:15.979 --> 08:17.245
        [HAJI LAUGHING]

08:17.247 --> 08:18.947
   AMANDA:
Oh, that duck.
                      [LAUGHING]

08:18.949 --> 08:19.948
I can't tell you,

08:19.950 --> 08:21.516
it was absolutely heavenly.

08:21.518 --> 08:23.484
       Why don't you ask
  Mrs. Nelson for the recipe?

08:23.486 --> 08:24.752
     The orange sauce, oh--

08:24.754 --> 08:26.888
         And I'd like the recipe
        for the creamed caramel.

08:26.890 --> 08:28.556
     You couldn't beat it.

08:28.558 --> 08:30.558
Shall we take our coffee
 into the living room?

08:30.560 --> 08:32.092
        Yes. Excuse us.

08:32.095 --> 08:33.395
                  TONY:
         Oh, that was wonderful.

08:33.397 --> 08:34.861
               Amanda,
         you don't remember--

08:34.864 --> 08:36.664
                       BELLOWS:
                      Excuse me.

08:36.666 --> 08:38.533
           Remember the sauce...

08:38.534 --> 08:39.567
         Ah-ah-ah-ah-ah.

08:41.438 --> 08:42.470
         Oh, that was wonderful.

08:42.472 --> 08:43.938
         I-- I'll help you clear
                the table.

08:43.941 --> 08:45.706
   Oh, it would only take me
           a second.

08:49.396 --> 08:51.796
Oh, I keep forgetting.

08:51.798 --> 08:53.198
          [BOTH LAUGH]

08:53.200 --> 08:55.333
            And believe me,
      I like it better this way.

08:55.335 --> 08:57.102
           Oh.

08:58.372 --> 09:00.772
   [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

09:01.541 --> 09:02.841
No, no.

09:02.843 --> 09:04.909
          Sit here, darling.
     You'll be more comfortable.

09:04.911 --> 09:06.711
               Oh, thanks.
Oh, Alfred, darling.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.580
     Look at that beautiful rug.

09:08.582 --> 09:09.664
 Beautiful.

09:09.666 --> 09:11.583
            Jeannie made it
         in her weaving class.

09:11.585 --> 09:13.835
                  Made it? Oh.

09:13.837 --> 09:15.503
 Allow me, dear.

09:18.058 --> 09:21.142
You're certainly a lucky man,
       Colonel Nelson.

09:21.144 --> 09:22.978
                I think so, sir.

09:22.980 --> 09:25.613
Last night we had meatloaf.

09:25.615 --> 09:26.614
                  [CHUCKLES]

09:26.616 --> 09:28.850
                 Alfred makes
             marvelous meatloaf.

09:28.852 --> 09:31.586
         [ALL LAUGHING]

09:31.588 --> 09:33.755
                Jeannie, that's
              a beautiful dress.

09:33.757 --> 09:34.823
           Where did you get it?

09:34.825 --> 09:36.590
Oh, thank you.
  I made it.

09:36.592 --> 09:38.342
                Oh, she makes
            all her own clothes.

09:39.246 --> 09:40.245
     Ma--?

09:40.247 --> 09:41.997
          Oh, for heaven's sake.

09:41.999 --> 09:43.664
    She wanted to make
   all of his uniforms,

09:43.666 --> 09:45.066
 but he wouldn't let her.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.787
                We had to draw
             the line somewhere.

09:48.789 --> 09:51.006
 You know she's gonna add
an extra room to the house?

09:51.008 --> 09:54.042
      What?
                 She's wonderful
                 with her hands.

09:54.044 --> 09:56.127
  And to think I was
against this marriage.

09:56.129 --> 09:58.463
    Why were you against
the marriage, Colonel Healey?

09:58.465 --> 09:59.797
     Well, I, uh--

09:59.799 --> 10:02.467
           He probably wanted
        to keep her for himself.

10:02.469 --> 10:03.935
          ROGER:
Yeah, well, I didn't think

10:03.937 --> 10:05.437
it was fair for one man
     to have her.

10:05.439 --> 10:07.806
It's hard to keep a girl
 like that bottled up.

10:07.808 --> 10:08.807
                 [LAUGHS]

10:10.727 --> 10:12.594
           I hate to break up
       such a beautiful evening,

10:12.596 --> 10:15.146
          but I think we should
         be running along. Okay?

10:15.148 --> 10:17.699
  I think that we should go too.
          Yeah.

10:17.701 --> 10:20.668
   Yes, I haven't done
this morning's dishes yet.

10:20.670 --> 10:22.570
             Funny, funny, dear.

10:22.572 --> 10:24.572
       Oh, you don't really have
           to go now, do you?

10:24.574 --> 10:26.707
There's no question about it,
       Colonel Nelson.

10:26.709 --> 10:29.577
 This marriage is the greatest
thing that ever happened to you.

10:29.579 --> 10:31.112
                 I agree, sir.

10:31.114 --> 10:32.497
       AMANDA:
The perfect marriage.

10:32.499 --> 10:34.232
 The perfect marriage.

10:34.234 --> 10:35.467
           The perfect marriage.

10:35.469 --> 10:38.169
 The perfect marriage.
 The perfect marriage.

10:41.908 --> 10:44.209
          Boy, was I ever wrong?
[LAUGHING]

10:44.211 --> 10:46.011
 I told you,
Major Healey.

10:46.013 --> 10:48.847
     Are you sure that's the way
          it's going to be?

10:48.849 --> 10:51.016
         You have seen it
       with your own eyes.

10:51.018 --> 10:53.685
    Can I ask you something?
                Yes.

10:53.687 --> 10:55.654
    Uh, do you know that girl
        that was my date?

10:55.656 --> 10:57.822
                Mm.
Well, I've never met her before.

10:57.824 --> 11:01.159
Uh, you wouldn't happen to have
her telephone number, would you?

11:01.161 --> 11:03.144
          It's okay.

11:04.497 --> 11:06.364
 You're sure you want to marry
         one of these?

11:06.366 --> 11:07.749
           Oh, yes.

11:07.751 --> 11:09.868
     You won't miss having
     the powers of a genie?

11:09.870 --> 11:10.902
            No.

11:10.904 --> 11:12.787
I will have something greater.

11:12.789 --> 11:14.839
   You know what this will do
        to your parents?

11:14.841 --> 11:16.441
             [♪♪♪]

11:16.443 --> 11:17.709
           Yes.

11:17.711 --> 11:20.078
       I will not tell them
   that you married a mortal.

11:20.080 --> 11:22.279
         I will tell them
      that you were killed

11:22.281 --> 11:23.965
      in a chariot accident.

11:23.967 --> 11:26.685
   Oh, thank you, Haji.

11:26.687 --> 11:28.419
   There's nothing more to say.

11:28.421 --> 11:30.488
      This is the last time
     I will see you, Jeannie.

11:30.490 --> 11:31.556
           Farewell.

11:31.558 --> 11:33.058
      Farewell, Haji.

11:33.060 --> 11:34.825
  [GIGGLING]
And thank you.

11:34.827 --> 11:36.994
    About that telephone number,
        I thought maybe we--

11:38.565 --> 11:39.830
          Oh.

11:39.832 --> 11:40.831
        [GIGGLES]

11:40.833 --> 11:42.534
      Oh, boy, was I ever wrong.

11:42.536 --> 11:43.968
         Whoa, was I ever wrong.

11:43.970 --> 11:45.870
Then you are no longer
against the marriage?

11:45.872 --> 11:47.838
         Why should I be against
          the perfect marriage?

11:47.840 --> 11:49.840
         It's the greatest thing
         to ever happen to Tony.

11:49.842 --> 11:51.576
      Oh, thank you.
             Hey, wait a minute.

11:51.578 --> 11:53.878
     Hey, we better get ready.
   We've got a wedding to go to.

11:53.880 --> 11:54.912
         Mm-hm.

11:54.914 --> 11:56.614
             [♪♪♪]

11:59.068 --> 12:01.452
             [♪♪♪]

12:01.454 --> 12:03.955
           Boy, my old buddy
            getting married.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.389
                  Gee, it's hard
                    to believe.

12:05.391 --> 12:07.058
              We sure had
      some great times together.

12:07.060 --> 12:08.459
       Yeah.

12:08.461 --> 12:10.762
 I have a feeling you'll be
getting married pretty soon.

12:10.764 --> 12:12.429
            Ah, so do I. I think
            I've found the girl,

12:12.431 --> 12:14.198
            but I-- I can't get
           her telephone number.

12:14.200 --> 12:15.399
  Uh, who's number?

12:15.401 --> 12:16.901
               I don't know,
          I haven't met her yet.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.402
           Listen, did you talk
              to Dr. Bellows

12:18.404 --> 12:19.670
      about getting married yet?

12:19.672 --> 12:21.939
No. No, I thought I'd wait
until after the honeymoon.

12:21.941 --> 12:23.540
      I didn't know
how he was gonna take it.

12:23.542 --> 12:24.742
                I wouldn't worry
                   about him.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.778
               He said it'll be
             a perfect marriage.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.312
     Hm. Yeah.

12:31.001 --> 12:32.633
      You're getting married?

12:32.635 --> 12:34.068
             Tonight?

12:34.070 --> 12:36.404
            Yes, sir. Uh, I have
             some leave accrued,

12:36.406 --> 12:38.373
       and I thought we'd fly up
          to Maryland tonight.

12:38.375 --> 12:39.773
         Yeah, I'm gonna be
           the best man.

12:39.775 --> 12:41.442
Well, I haven't met
the young lady yet,

12:41.444 --> 12:43.244
but if she's the right kind
     of wife for you,

12:43.246 --> 12:45.296
it could be exactly
what you've needed.

12:45.298 --> 12:47.832
       Uh, believe me, sir,
    she's a most unusual girl.

12:47.834 --> 12:49.650
        Unusual?
She puts on his slippers,

12:49.652 --> 12:51.719
     and she's building on
  an extra room in the house.

12:52.606 --> 12:54.355
I'm very anxious to meet her.

12:54.357 --> 12:56.257
        ROGER:
     Oh, you will.
She's going to make you

12:56.259 --> 12:57.692
the most marvelous
   duck dinner.

12:57.694 --> 12:59.260
  We're gonna have to have
        that dinner

12:59.262 --> 13:00.562
 right after your honeymoon.

13:00.564 --> 13:02.530
      I've got to get
that girl's telephone number.

13:02.532 --> 13:03.698
    BELLOWS:
Are you planning

13:03.700 --> 13:05.150
       on a large family?

13:05.152 --> 13:06.317
          Oh, yes, sir.

13:06.319 --> 13:08.036
     We both love children.

13:08.038 --> 13:09.803
Well, congratulations.

13:09.805 --> 13:11.289
       Thank you very much, sir.

13:11.291 --> 13:12.824
            Children?

13:12.826 --> 13:15.226
  Why did you summon me again?

13:15.228 --> 13:17.829
   Oh, I am sorry
to trouble you, Haji,

13:17.831 --> 13:19.730
   but we are
a little worried.

13:19.732 --> 13:22.466
     A little worried?
     We were panicking.

13:22.468 --> 13:23.935
   So if Jeannie marries
         a mortal,

13:23.937 --> 13:25.602
    are their children
    mortals or genies?

13:25.604 --> 13:26.603
                    Mortals.

13:26.605 --> 13:27.705
     Ah.
            Ah.

13:27.707 --> 13:29.373
              Ah, but sometimes,
             they may be genies.

13:29.375 --> 13:30.942
      There's no way of knowing.

13:30.944 --> 13:33.211
     But we've got to know.
Can we look in the future again?

13:33.213 --> 13:35.213
             I am late for
       an appointment in Samara.

13:35.215 --> 13:36.247
Oh, please, please.

13:36.249 --> 13:37.882
          Please.

13:37.884 --> 13:39.717
   Please.

13:39.719 --> 13:41.652
               Uh, very well.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.155
                    [WAILS]

13:45.157 --> 13:46.958
                  [MUTTERING]

13:48.728 --> 13:49.727
             TONY:
          Yeah. Uh...

13:49.729 --> 13:52.229
   "Insert flap A
    into flap B,

13:52.231 --> 13:56.233
     after sealing C
 into position F. And--"

13:56.235 --> 13:58.669
 Yeah, now, we've already
    done that, right?

13:58.671 --> 14:00.237
         [SIGHS]

14:00.239 --> 14:03.040
Uh, let's see now, "Do not
fasten the widgets together

14:03.042 --> 14:04.876
until a square has been..."

14:06.212 --> 14:07.912
         Jeannie.

14:07.914 --> 14:09.413
       Would you?

14:09.415 --> 14:12.483
      Oh, yes, dear. Darling,
  Daddy's trying to concentrate.

14:12.485 --> 14:13.651
     [CHUCKLES]
    That's right.

14:13.653 --> 14:15.119
Can you fix it, Daddy?

14:15.121 --> 14:17.488
    Oh, sure, honey.
 There's nothing to it.

14:17.490 --> 14:19.223
It says, uh, right here--
        It says,

14:19.225 --> 14:20.625
    "Any child
 over the age of 7

14:20.627 --> 14:22.326
can assemble this house
    in 10 minutes."

14:22.328 --> 14:25.529
  Oh, I am sure it's going to be
      a beautiful dollhouse.

14:25.531 --> 14:27.498
          Come, Anthony.
           Help Mommy.

14:27.500 --> 14:28.833
       Now, let's see.

14:28.835 --> 14:30.601
        "Do not fasten
     the widgets together

14:30.603 --> 14:33.037
 until a square has been formed
        by folding Z--"

14:33.039 --> 14:34.338
         Uh, "Z over Y."

14:34.340 --> 14:36.240
  That shouldn't be hard, huh?

14:36.242 --> 14:38.176
               Um...

14:38.178 --> 14:41.312
       Now, we dealt with Z.

14:41.314 --> 14:43.748
  They never tell you which...

14:43.750 --> 14:45.449
  It's in the diagram, I know.

14:49.923 --> 14:50.955
             [CHUCKLES]

14:50.957 --> 14:52.156
          I tell you what.

14:52.158 --> 14:54.125
    Why don't you study this
      for a little while?

14:54.127 --> 14:56.460
     Your daddy's got some
   phone calls to make, huh?

14:59.132 --> 15:01.683
    Did Daddy help you again?

15:01.685 --> 15:02.934
             Yes.

15:02.936 --> 15:05.019
    Why don't you go ahead,
             do it.

15:05.021 --> 15:07.538
         All right.

15:09.492 --> 15:12.110
      Boy, what a great house.

15:12.112 --> 15:13.978
            Oh!

15:13.980 --> 15:16.364
  I told you never
to do that, darling.

15:16.366 --> 15:18.766
But I wanted my dollhouse.

15:18.768 --> 15:20.434
       Oh, please, darling.

15:20.436 --> 15:21.802
        If your father knew
            about this,

15:21.804 --> 15:23.904
   it would make him terribly,
        terribly nervous.

15:23.906 --> 15:27.274
    Please, promise me, never,
   never, ever to do it again.

15:27.276 --> 15:28.342
          And, Anthony--

15:28.344 --> 15:30.010
BELLOWS: Yoo-hoo.
AMANDA: Yoo-hoo!

15:30.012 --> 15:31.012
                Oh.

15:31.014 --> 15:32.779
  Oh, Dr. Bellows.

15:32.781 --> 15:34.448
  Hello.
            Well--

15:34.450 --> 15:36.617
Forgive us for dropping in
 like this, Mrs. Nelson,

15:36.619 --> 15:38.152
but we were just passing by.

15:38.154 --> 15:39.520
        We were nowhere
        near the place,

15:39.522 --> 15:41.155
         we just wanted
      to see the children.

15:41.157 --> 15:42.390
             Hello.

15:42.392 --> 15:45.826
      Ah. Amanda,
look how they've grown.

15:45.828 --> 15:47.161
And this is for you,
     young man.

15:47.163 --> 15:48.962
 Come over here next
to your Uncle Alfred.

15:48.964 --> 15:50.731
Now, look, let's lean
 down here and see.

15:50.733 --> 15:52.099
  I bet you can't guess
       what it is.

15:52.101 --> 15:53.534
                   How lovely.
     Well, come on.

15:53.536 --> 15:54.668
   An airplane?

15:54.670 --> 15:56.170
                  Ah, now,
            what makes you think

15:56.172 --> 15:57.704
             it's an airplane?

15:59.442 --> 16:01.909
           Look, a fire engine.

16:01.911 --> 16:03.461
 I wanted an airplane.

16:03.463 --> 16:04.963
          [GASPS]

16:04.965 --> 16:07.365
            He-- He's just crazy
             about fire engines.

16:07.367 --> 16:08.399
          [LAUGHS]

16:08.401 --> 16:09.550
                    Darling,

16:09.552 --> 16:11.285
                this is for you.

16:11.287 --> 16:12.953
Thank you, Mrs. Bellows.

16:12.955 --> 16:14.288
                 You're welcome.

16:14.290 --> 16:16.023
      He's hungry.

16:16.025 --> 16:17.675
             Yeah, you give him
                 a cracker.

16:17.677 --> 16:19.410
       Ah, look, Amanda.

16:19.412 --> 16:20.478
  She's trying to feed him.

16:20.480 --> 16:21.845
          [LAUGHS]
            Isn't that sweet?

16:21.847 --> 16:24.014
    Won't you come in the house
     and have a cup of coffee?

16:24.016 --> 16:25.516
           Tony is inside.
     Well, thank you,

16:25.518 --> 16:27.251
but we just had some coffee,
        but anyway.

16:27.253 --> 16:28.419
            JEANNIE:
        Please, come in.

16:28.421 --> 16:30.120
       AMANDA:
Oh, thank you, dear.

16:30.122 --> 16:32.122
             [♪♪♪]

16:41.334 --> 16:43.201
          Oh. How are you doing,
               Dr. Bellows?

16:43.203 --> 16:45.136
  Forgive us for intruding,
          colonel,

16:45.138 --> 16:46.838
    but we've just had
   to see the children.

16:46.840 --> 16:48.706
      They brought them the most
            wonderful toys.

16:48.708 --> 16:50.441
     Oh, now, you shouldn't
        have done that.

16:50.443 --> 16:52.543
    Every time you come here,
      you spoil them rotten.

16:52.545 --> 16:54.412
Oh, don't be silly.
   We enjoy it.

16:54.414 --> 16:55.930
They're wonderful children.

16:55.932 --> 16:58.850
           Oh, yes.
 They take after their father.

16:58.852 --> 17:00.485
                 They take after
                  their mother.

17:00.487 --> 17:01.586
 Let's watch them play.

17:01.588 --> 17:02.987
                 Uh, well,
          how 'bout some coffee?

17:02.989 --> 17:04.422
   We just had some coffee.

17:04.424 --> 17:06.624
       Have some coffee, sir.
      You haven't had Jeannie's.

17:06.626 --> 17:09.226
 She makes extra-special coffee.
     Have some coffee, please.

17:09.228 --> 17:10.928
         No, I--
   I swore I just saw--

17:10.930 --> 17:12.229
    Oh, no, no, no,
    it couldn't be,

17:12.231 --> 17:13.531
                      No, no.

17:13.532 --> 17:15.465
   Well, didn't I bring
 your son a fire engine?

17:15.468 --> 17:17.067
       Yes, why don't we have--?
      Well, I--

17:17.069 --> 17:18.603
       BOTH:
        Oh!

17:18.605 --> 17:20.271
        Jeannie, if you knew
             about this,

17:20.272 --> 17:21.439
    why didn't you tell me?

17:21.441 --> 17:22.874
    I did not wish
    to worry you.

17:22.876 --> 17:24.157
          Huh? Worry me?

17:24.160 --> 17:26.492
       Major Nel-- Uh--

17:26.494 --> 17:28.529
         Well, look.
          Your son.

17:28.531 --> 17:31.632
 He's flying through the air,
and it's not even an airplane.

17:31.634 --> 17:33.901
   Why, it's a fire engine.
Make him come down.

17:33.903 --> 17:36.070
 Yes. Now, Anthony--
Jeannie, do something.

17:36.072 --> 17:37.571
    Anthony! Anthony!

17:37.573 --> 17:39.040
       Anthony!
 Come down this minute.

17:39.042 --> 17:40.808
[STAMMERING INDISTINCTLY]
             Oh!

17:40.810 --> 17:42.009
        Stop it!

17:42.011 --> 17:43.310
      It's starting again.

17:43.312 --> 17:45.179
           First him,
   and now it's his children.

17:45.181 --> 17:46.446
         Listen to your mother.

17:46.448 --> 17:48.082
   Come on, Anthony,
   I'm not kidding.

17:48.084 --> 17:50.000
It's one of those things
  that just happened.

17:50.002 --> 17:51.969
Now, Anthony, you come down
    right this minute!

17:51.971 --> 17:53.937
      BELLOWS:
        Oh.

17:53.939 --> 17:54.938
        [GASPS]

17:54.940 --> 17:56.340
         Oh, no.

17:56.342 --> 17:59.026
   You're not going to get
out of it this time, colonel!

17:59.028 --> 18:00.828
                      AMANDA:
                   Get him down!

18:00.830 --> 18:01.995
         I'll get him over here.

18:01.997 --> 18:04.398
 Anthony, you come down
   right this minute.

18:04.400 --> 18:05.599
Listen to your mother.

18:05.601 --> 18:07.618
                  You're going
               to hurt yourself.

18:07.620 --> 18:09.587
       Jeannie,
would you do something?

18:09.589 --> 18:12.090
     I told you he was hungry.

18:12.092 --> 18:13.958
   Anthony, you come down here!

18:13.960 --> 18:16.294
        TONY:
Anthony, you come down
  right this minute.

18:16.296 --> 18:17.995
             TONY:
Jeannie, would you do something?

18:17.997 --> 18:19.797
        They're going
    to court-martial him.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.732
           They're going
       to court-martial him!

18:21.734 --> 18:23.734
            You've seen he's had
           no luck with his son,

18:23.736 --> 18:25.669
        but his daughter will be
                a genie.

18:25.671 --> 18:27.705
     Now, you must tell him that
        before you marry him.

18:27.707 --> 18:29.107
               It is so written.

18:29.109 --> 18:30.408
   Oh, yes, yes,

18:30.410 --> 18:32.143
  I will tell him.
             Good.

18:32.145 --> 18:34.878
                I must go now,
              and I'll warn you.

18:34.880 --> 18:36.614
                I warn you,

18:36.616 --> 18:39.117
        do not disturb me again.

18:39.119 --> 18:40.902
             [♪♪♪]

18:44.607 --> 18:46.073
You've got to get hold of Tony.

18:46.075 --> 18:47.275
                  What for?

18:47.277 --> 18:49.110
 What for? To tell him
 the marriage is off.

18:49.112 --> 18:51.012
                Oh, why would
            the marriage be off?

18:51.014 --> 18:53.080
    Why would the--?
 You saw what happened.

18:53.082 --> 18:55.516
       Well, yes, but I will not
             let it happen.

18:55.518 --> 18:56.750
            I love him too much.

18:56.752 --> 18:59.620
Well, if you're not going
   to tell him, I am.

19:07.430 --> 19:09.263
            [GROANS]

19:09.265 --> 19:11.565
          Ow! Jeannie!

19:11.567 --> 19:12.933
            Jeannie!

19:12.935 --> 19:15.403
             [GASPS]
       Forgive me, Major Healey.

19:15.405 --> 19:16.804
         Oh, forgive--
        Are you kidding?

19:16.806 --> 19:18.906
           Get me down
       from here right now!

19:18.908 --> 19:20.474
                 As soon as
            the wedding is over.

19:20.476 --> 19:22.676
   Oh, Jeannie, you've got to
   get me out of this place.

19:22.678 --> 19:24.244
                    Oh, I--

19:24.246 --> 19:26.480
  You will be all right there
        until we return.

19:26.482 --> 19:27.615
          All right?

19:27.617 --> 19:30.984
     I am truly sorry
you cannot be our best man.

19:30.986 --> 19:32.052
            [YELPS]

19:32.054 --> 19:33.186
      Goodbye.

19:33.188 --> 19:34.822
            Goodb--

19:34.824 --> 19:37.024
    Oh, Jeannie, don't go!

19:37.026 --> 19:39.393
           Not now!
             Aagh!

19:40.847 --> 19:41.879
             Jeannie.

19:42.681 --> 19:44.281
                   Jeannie?

19:44.917 --> 19:46.317
                 Jeannie!

19:46.319 --> 19:47.417
I am ready, master.

19:47.419 --> 19:48.485
                     Oh.

19:48.487 --> 19:50.387
              Oh, good, good.
              Well, I'll, uh--

19:50.389 --> 19:52.489
       I'll pack a suitcase,
   and we'll be on our way, huh?

19:54.693 --> 19:55.726
                     Oh.

19:55.728 --> 19:57.094
  We are all packed, master.

19:57.096 --> 19:59.196
                 [LAUGHING]
            Yes, I can see that.

19:59.198 --> 20:00.831
      Well, thank you very much.

20:00.833 --> 20:02.466
          Oh, has Roger called?

20:02.468 --> 20:04.168
           Oh, no.

20:04.170 --> 20:05.569
                      No.

20:05.571 --> 20:07.771
  But he ran out of Dr. Bellow''
       office this morning,

20:07.773 --> 20:08.973
   and I haven't seen him since.

20:08.975 --> 20:10.274
                I-- I wonder
             where he could be.

20:10.276 --> 20:11.608
Perhaps he is tied up.

20:11.610 --> 20:13.377
             Hm? Yeah, yeah.

20:13.379 --> 20:15.746
      Well, he probably found
  that girl's phone number, huh?

20:15.748 --> 20:17.514
            We'll just have
       to get along without him.

20:17.516 --> 20:18.916
 Well, that is what
    I told him.

20:18.918 --> 20:20.417
                Huh?
    Oh, nothing.

20:20.419 --> 20:22.286
                     Okay.

20:22.288 --> 20:24.622
             [♪♪♪]

20:26.292 --> 20:29.193
    The Man from U.N.C.L.E.
always gets out of these things.

20:30.479 --> 20:31.679
Okay, Jeannie,
  I'm ready.

20:31.681 --> 20:33.147
              Shall I blink us
                to Maryland?

20:33.149 --> 20:34.148
  [CHUCKLING]
    No. No.

20:34.150 --> 20:35.883
We're gonna fly
 to Maryland.

20:35.885 --> 20:38.251
From now on, I don't want you
   to use anymore tricks.

20:38.253 --> 20:39.953
        Oh, but it is so simple,
                 master.

20:39.955 --> 20:41.388
       No.

20:41.390 --> 20:43.891
In a few hours, you're not
gonna be a genie anymore.

20:43.893 --> 20:45.859
And you may as well start
   getting used to it.

20:45.861 --> 20:47.360
                Yes, master.

20:47.362 --> 20:48.962
      Okay.

20:48.964 --> 20:50.030
                      Oh,

20:50.032 --> 20:53.233
               I have waited
             so long for this.

20:53.235 --> 20:55.235
      Mrs. Anthony Nelson.

20:56.605 --> 20:59.272
We should've done this
   a long time ago.

20:59.274 --> 21:01.608
          Oh, I want to make you
               a good wife.

21:04.279 --> 21:08.182
I have a feeling we're not gonna
   have a worry in the world.

21:08.184 --> 21:10.718
     Let me call Roger
       one more time.

21:10.720 --> 21:11.852
  I also have a feeling

21:11.854 --> 21:13.854
that something really important
         hung him up.

21:17.277 --> 21:19.777
          [SCREAMING]

21:19.779 --> 21:22.480
     Oh, Jeannie, wait till
     I get my hands on you.

21:22.482 --> 21:24.014
 Oh, what am I calling her for?

21:24.016 --> 21:26.350
       Jeannie, Jeannie,
    she's not gonna help me.

21:26.352 --> 21:27.918
              Haji.

21:27.920 --> 21:29.387
               Haji!

21:30.856 --> 21:32.657
             Haji!

21:32.659 --> 21:34.992
Ah, you can't hear me, can you?
     You want to know why?

21:34.994 --> 21:36.694
    Because you're deaf!

21:36.696 --> 21:38.996
      You're a deaf,
      dirty old man!

21:38.998 --> 21:40.898
    And your father's
    a dirty old man!

21:40.900 --> 21:43.167
  And you're a coward,
  you hear? A coward!

21:43.169 --> 21:44.735
    Boy, do you know
   what's gonna happen

21:44.737 --> 21:46.270
when I get my hands on you?

21:48.007 --> 21:50.908
            Now we shall see

21:50.910 --> 21:53.343
          who is the coward.

21:53.345 --> 21:54.478
               [WAILING]

21:54.480 --> 21:56.079
     I'll tell you
   who's the coward.

21:56.081 --> 21:58.566
I am, but at least, I'm not like
    a genie, I keep my word.

21:58.568 --> 22:01.235
  Are you saying that a genie
    does not keep his word?

22:01.237 --> 22:03.037
       You told Jeannie
   she couldn't marry Tony,

22:03.039 --> 22:04.705
      unless she told him
      one of his children

22:04.707 --> 22:05.722
   was going to be a genie.

22:06.692 --> 22:08.292
             That

22:08.294 --> 22:11.245
        is so written.

22:11.247 --> 22:12.713
   Yeah, but she erased it.

22:12.715 --> 22:14.782
    She's getting married,
   and she didn't tell him.

22:14.784 --> 22:16.783
             [♪♪♪]

22:20.172 --> 22:22.106
      Oh. Haji. You're not
      through cooking yet.

22:27.013 --> 22:28.012
         He-- He doesn't answer.

22:28.014 --> 22:29.613
I did not think he would.

22:29.615 --> 22:30.781
   Let us go, master.

22:30.783 --> 22:31.982
         This is not like Roger.

22:31.984 --> 22:33.483
    We must not miss
       the plane.

22:33.485 --> 22:34.484
               You're right.

22:34.486 --> 22:35.986
               [CHUCKLES]

22:35.988 --> 22:37.021
          You're always right.

22:37.023 --> 22:38.089
    [GIGGLES]

22:39.925 --> 22:40.957
   H-Haji.

22:40.959 --> 22:42.158
       Uh, we were just leaving.

22:42.160 --> 22:43.159
      Where are you going?

22:43.161 --> 22:44.294
To Maryland.

22:44.296 --> 22:45.429
             Um, to get married.

22:45.431 --> 22:47.031
        Has she told you
      about your children?

22:47.033 --> 22:48.232
       My children?

22:48.234 --> 22:49.400
         It is nothing.

22:49.402 --> 22:51.986
           Tell him.
       I was going to.

22:51.988 --> 22:53.821
 Well, what about my children?

22:55.241 --> 22:56.340
           Tell him.

22:57.293 --> 22:59.626
            Well,

22:59.628 --> 23:02.429
      some of our children
         may be genies.

23:03.666 --> 23:05.382
     "Some of our children
        may be genies"?

23:06.085 --> 23:07.084
          Some of our children--

23:07.086 --> 23:08.085
           Are you sure?

23:08.087 --> 23:09.553
   Yes, master.

23:09.555 --> 23:11.755
 Oh, that's great. We're right
     back where we started.

23:11.757 --> 23:13.557
   Can you imagine what chaos
        life is gonna be

23:13.559 --> 23:15.358
          with a bunch
    of little genies around?

23:17.463 --> 23:19.663
                    You are
               my favorite genie

23:19.665 --> 23:21.348
          and an adorable child,

23:21.350 --> 23:25.035
but do not bother me again.

23:25.805 --> 23:27.003
             Jeannie.

23:28.607 --> 23:30.474
        Are you all right?
        Are you all right?

23:30.476 --> 23:33.243
I will go unpack, master.

23:33.245 --> 23:35.011
                Oh, Jeannie,
              I'm sorry, but--

23:35.013 --> 23:36.246
    Well, you should've told me.

23:36.248 --> 23:37.514
     Yes, master.

23:37.516 --> 23:38.782
                You understand,
                  don't you?

23:38.784 --> 23:40.250
    Yes, master.

23:40.252 --> 23:42.018
              Where's Roger?

23:42.020 --> 23:43.120
        Roger.

23:43.122 --> 23:44.721
                  Yeah.

23:44.723 --> 23:47.074
 I forgot Major Healey!

23:48.795 --> 23:51.561
    Major Healey?
    Major Healey?

23:51.563 --> 23:52.863
    Jeannie, what is this place?

23:52.865 --> 23:54.564
Oh, this is where
   I left him.

23:54.566 --> 23:55.632
           Oh!

23:57.569 --> 23:59.003
          Oh.

24:02.008 --> 24:03.240
      [YELPS]

24:03.242 --> 24:05.042
     Major Healey!

24:05.945 --> 24:07.311
                   Roger?

24:07.313 --> 24:09.880
             ROGER:
     Oh, is that you, Tony?

24:09.882 --> 24:11.849
   Hey, that Haji isn't such
      a bad guy after all.

24:11.851 --> 24:13.450
       I asked him
for Sally's phone number,

24:13.452 --> 24:14.718
and look what he gave me.

24:14.720 --> 24:16.520
         Mm. Oh.

24:19.959 --> 24:22.126
            Mm. Mm.

24:22.128 --> 24:24.561
       Oh, hi, Jeannie.
 Would you like a marshmallow?

24:24.563 --> 24:26.430
             [♪♪♪]

24:28.801 --> 24:30.801
             [♪♪♪]
